1. String is a non primitive data type because size is not fixed.

2. String is a sequence of characters(Array of characters)

3. String is a class.
Syntax :
public final class String entends Object{

}

4. we can call string in Four ways
a) String
String s = "Learn";
b) String
String s = new String();
c) StringBuffer
d) StringBuilder

5. String is a immutable object.